file.title: AMM PART II-1285 - CHAPTER 20-30-06-02 - MISCELLANEOUS PRODUCTS - MAINTENANCE PRACTICES

page.data: AIRCRAFT MAINTENANCE MANUAL MISCELLANEOUS PRODUCTS - MAINTENANCE PRACTICES EFFECTIVITY: ALL 1. General A. This subchapter gives a list of the products approved to be used on, and for the servicing of, the aircraft, with their most usual suppliers. B. Refer to the correct procedure to use the products, with the practices for filling, charging, lubricating, or other applications, given in the chapters listed below. C. Products with the same specification MIL-, FED. SPEC., but of different marks must not be mixed. D. Possible alternative products are listed opposite the same group of chapters where the indicated product(s) is(are) referenced. E. Products listed on the QPL (Qualified Products List) as per MIL specifications referred to in this subchapter are automatically approved to be used on the aircraft. F. The supplier/manufacturer addresses are listed in AMM MPP 20-30-00/200. EMB-145 - AMM 1285 General 20-30-06 Page 1 of 8 Rev 54 - Apr 27/18 Copyright ÃÂ© by Embraer S.A.
